{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01AibVxNnUtcwEAWNgoFEC1m","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have all the information I need. Let me write all four files. I'll start by writing the tests, then the implementation.\n\nFor the biome linter:\n- `indentStyle`: \"space\", `indentWidth`: 2 (already using 2 spaces)\n- `recommended`: true — there might be some rules about unused variables, explicit types, etc.\n- `next`: \"recommended\" — Next.js specific rules\n\nLet me be careful with biome rules:\n- No unused variables\n- Explicit function return types\n- No non-null assertion (might be an issue with `!` operator)\n\n\n- `organizeImports` is on - imports will be auto-organized\n\nFor the `!` non-null assertion in `seriesMap.get(label)!.push(...)`, biome might warn. I'll refactor to safely access the map value without the non-null assertion operator, using a conditional check or optional chaining approach instead.\n\nWriting the implementation files... Refactoring the map initialization logic...\n\nNow I'm checking the imports to make sure nothing's unused, and I should remove that `topLabels` Set since it's not being used. For the response handling, I'll stick with `Response.json` like the events list route does, since it's available globally in Node 18+ and doesn't require an extra import from Next.js.\n\nThe mock pattern in the tests relies on vitest hoisting, which lifts the mock setup before imports happen, so that should work fine. I need to make sure the `TrendsQuerySpec` interface is properly exported from my `buildTrendsQuery` function.\n\nLet me think through the ClickHouse query details more carefully—specifically how timestamp comparisons work with string parameters and what type `toDate(DateTime64)` returns.\n\nIn ClickHouse, `toDate(DateTime64)` gives back a `Date` type that comes through as a string like \"2026-04-01\", and `toMonday(DateTime64)` works the same way. For the